sql:
SELECT commit_id, commit_message
FROM commits
WHERE branch_name = 'main';

external_knowledge:
- "master craftsmen" is a metaphorical expression for top contributors or skilled developers; 
- "weave more than 10 lines of code" means having an average of more than 10 lines changed per commit; 
- "repository 12345" refers to the specific repository being analyzed, identified by its ID; 
- "dawn of 2023 and its dusk" represents the start and end of the year 2023, symbolically expressing the beginning and end of the time frame in question.

- 'master builders' refers to the top contributors in each repository (construction site);
- 'blueprints' refers to commits;
- 'lines added', 'lines changed', and 'lines deleted' refer to the total number of lines added, changed, and deleted by each committer, respectively.
